</div>
<div class="span11 buffer">

<p>25c Inc. simplifies social micro-donations.</p>

<p>You truly appreciate that blog article?  Value that helpful comment?  That open-source contributor?  That volunteer or personal cause?  It's just one click to show your appreciation -- by pledging a quarter (everyone can spare a quarter).  Or multiples thereof and possibly daily or weekly. 

<p>At 25c, we are working on ideas to help shift the incentive system towards compensating for "value to you" more than "value to a third party" such as an advertiser.  Because we believe that if you directly support what you value, you will see more of such in the future.  And over time, that shift can grow to be very meaningful in a very qualitative way.</P>

<p>Our first offering is the +25c Button&trade;.  Anyone who has a website, blog, or Youtube video can easily embed the +25c Button into it following on our step-by-step instructions and start receiving 25c pledges in a breeze.  Those who don't have their own website can simply create a profile page on 25c.com to collect 25c pledges.</p>

<P>The +25c Button empowers people to easily & directly support what they value.  Effectively a “Super Like”, the +25c Button combines a "Like" with a 25c pledge.  Or multiples thereof because the +25c Button is “multi-one-click”: each click pledges 25 cents.</p>

<p>25c Inc. is a privately held company located in San Francisco, California.  Founded by Sylvio Drouin, Lionel Jingles, Francis Li, Ruza Markov, and Martin Roscheisen, the company operates a social "value graph" micro-payment pledge processing service.  The company owns a rapidly growing patent portfolio around social micro-donations.</p>

